review_blob: Chocolate brown and little head. Less aroma but maltyness. Not really enjoyable right now. Taste some errors. May be my taste buds but this was not the stout for me. Prefer my stout bigger and better.
Chocolate brown with a little cute little foam head. Enjoyable but lack some complexity to be a big beer.
Pour brown&reddish; with a coars foam. Half fruity without getting to sweet. Nice aroma and taste but may lack some of the complexness for me. But overall a very good beer!

This beer is probably some kind of historical beer before the discovered hops. Gruut was the spice mix they used instead. Nice experiment but for my taste it lacks the hops balance. It has a nice apperance but the taste and palate is rather disapointing.

Pours modestly with a small head.  Appealing smell, and slow attack but really kicks in with a nice solid but balanced coffee and chocolate aroma. A big beer to be 4.5% vol. Hop is nicely balanced and I would like another one.
